<DIV4 N="3" TYPE="section">
<HEAD>&sect; III.</HEAD>
<P>It was in the mid&s;t of th$&s;$ ho&s;tilities that Richard &s;ucceeded to the thron$ of Eng$a$d, which he a&s;cended without th$ $$a$t oppo&s;ition; and the c$remony of his coronation was fixed for the &s;ixteenth day of July. Mean $word$ $word$ created his favou$$te uncl$ Thomas of Wode&s;toke con&s;table of Eng|l$$$, $$ring the mino$$ty of the earl of Here$ord, who was entitled to that $word$ by he$$$itary rig$t. The duke of Lanca&s;ter at the &s;ame time laid claim t$ &s;$v$r$l $$$ices, on the day of co$onation, in right of his decea&s;ed wi$e $word$ as $$rl of $word$ he claimed the dignity o$ lo$d high &s;teward of $word$ as $word$ of $word$ h$ h$d a right to carry the &s;wo$d of &s;tate called $word$ and as earl of $word$ to be the king's carver. The&s;e preten&s;ions, b$i$g examined in counc$$, were $ound ju&s;t, and allowed accordingly; and t$en $e &s;$t by the king's $word$ as &s;t$ward of England, to examine the $laims of o$$er n$bl$m$n, $ho pretend$d right to perform different functions at that &s;ol$mnity. On the eve o$ the coronation, the king rode with a pom|pous cavalcade through the &s;treets of London, from the Tower to his palace at We$$min$$er. Next day h$ walk$d from thence in proce&s;&s;ion to the abbey|ch$r$h at W$$tmi$&s;ter; a$d, a&s;$ending a &s;caffold erected for that purpo&s;e, t$$k the u&s;ual oath, whi$h was admini&s;tred for that purpo&s;e by the arch|bi&s;hop, who afterwards pro$$eded to the ceremony of unction and coronation. Then the p$elate$ began to celebrate high-ma&s;s, and during that &s;ervice the $ing receiv$d the homage of all the lay nobility: divine wor&s;hip being per|formed, they returned to the pal$ce, and &s;pent the remainder of the day in<NOTE PLACE="marg">Rymer.</NOTE> $$$&s;ting and joy. On this occ$&s;ion, the king created his uncle Thomas, earl of B$$kin$ham; H$nry lord P$r$y, earl of Northumberland; John of Mowbr$y, earl of Nottingham; and Guichard d' Angle, earl of Huntingdon. The bi&s;hops of London and Sar