<PB N="248" REF="2500">
and Burgundians. Remarkab$$ &s;iege of Melun. &sect; <HI>LIII.</HI> Henry enters Paris in triump$. &sect; <HI>LIV.</HI> Decree of $he council of France again&s;t the murderers of the duke of Burgundy. &sect; <HI>LV.</HI> Henry returns to England. &sect; <HI>LVI.</HI> The duke of Cl$rence is defeated and $$ain at Bauge. &sect; <HI>LVII.</HI> Henry's tran&s;action with James king of $cotland. &sect; <HI>LVIII.</HI> His third expedition into France. &sect; <HI>LIX.</HI> D$$perate d$fence of the garri&s;on of Meaux. &sect; <HI>LX.</HI> The queen delivered of a &s;on at Wina&s;or. &sect; <HI>LXI.</HI> Henry is &s;eized with a dangerous di&s;temper. His la&s;t addre&s;s to his nobles. <HI>LXII.</HI> His death and character.</P>
