<DIV3 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<PB N="426" REF="4360">
<HEAD>CHAP. VII.</HEAD>
<ARGUMENT>
<P>&sect; <HI>I.</HI> Edward <HI>V.</HI> procl$imed king. &sect; <HI>II.</HI> The duke of Glouce&s;ter con&s;ults with his friends at Northampton. &sect; <HI>III.</HI> Writes a letter of condolance to the quee$. &sect; <HI>IV.</HI> Arre&s;ts the earl of Rivers, S$r Richard Gray, and Sir Thomas Vaughan. &sect; <HI>V.</HI> The queen takes &s;anctuary in We&s;tmin&s;ter. &sect; <HI>VI.</HI> Richard duke of Glou|ce&s;ter declared protector of the king and kingdom. &sect; <HI>VII.</HI> Young Edward and $is brother the duke of York are lodged in the Tower of London. &sect; <HI>VIII.</HI> Ri|vers, Grey, and Vaughan, are beheaded at Pontefract. &sect; <HI>IX.</HI> Reports &s;pread by the emi&s;&s;aries of Richard. &sect; <HI>X.</HI> He di$ides his council. &sect; <HI>XI.</HI> Orders Ha&s;|tings to be arre&s;ted and beheaded, without form of trial. &sect; <HI>XII.</HI> Jane Shore does public penance. &sect; <HI>XIII.</HI> Doctor Shaw's &s;ermon in prai&s;e of Richard. &sect; <HI>XIV.</HI> The d$ke of Buckingham $arrangues the Londoners in Guildball. &sect; <HI>XV.</HI> Ri|chard is proclaimed king. &sect; <HI>XVI.</HI> Is crowned at We&s;tmin&s;ter. &sect; <HI>XVII.</HI> Sends $$ba&s;&s;adors to different parts of the continent. &sect; <HI>XVIII.</HI> Death of the young princes in the Tower. &sect; <HI>XIX.</HI> Richard's &s;on is created prince of Wales. &sect; <HI>XX.</HI> The duke of Buckingham, and Morton bi&s;hop of Ely, contrive a &s;cheme in favour of the earl of Richmond. &sect; <HI>XXI.</HI> The queen dowager approves the &s;cheme. &sect; <HI>XXII.</HI> The duke of Buckingham le$ies forces in private. &sect; <HI>XXIII.</HI> The duke of Britta$y promi&s;es to a&s;&s;i&s;t the earl of Richmond. &sect; <HI>XXIV.</HI> Open rupture be|tween the king and the duke of Buckingham. &sect; <HI>XXV$</HI> Who is de&s;erted, betrayed, and put to death. &sect; <HI>XXVI.</HI> The earl of Richmond attempts to make a de&s;cent upon England. &sect; <HI>XXVII.</HI> Proceedings in parliament. &sect; <HI>XXVIII.</HI> Richard co$cludes a treaty with Peter de Landois, mini&s;ter of the duke of Brittany. &sect; <HI>XXIX.</HI> Death of the prince of Wales. &sect; <HI>XXX.</HI> The earl of Richmond e&s;|capes into France. &sect; <HI>XXXI.</HI> Richard makes advances to the queen dowager. &sect; <HI>XXXII.</HI> Who is per&s;uaded to leave the &s;anctuary. Death of queen Anne. &sect; <HI>XXXIII.</HI> Richard makes his addre&s;&s;es to his niece Elizabeth. &sect; <HI>XXXIV.</HI> Henry earl of Richmond prepares for his voyage to England. &sect; <HI>XXXV.</HI> Lands at Milford in Wales. &sect; <HI>XXXVI.</HI> He meets king Richard at Bo&s;worth. &sect; <HI>XXXVII.</HI> Where $e obtains a complete victory. The death of Richard. &sect; <HI>XXXVIII.</HI> His character.</P>
