;graced. &sect; <HI>LXXVI.</HI> Francis con|cludes a treaty with the emperor at Madrid, and is &s;et at liberty. &sect; <HI>LXXVII.</HI> He engages in a league with the pope, and the Venetians, who endeavour to engage Henry in the &s;ame alliance. &sect; <HI>LXXVIII.</HI> The pope is taken pri&s;oner, and Rome &s;acked by the Imperiali&s;ts. &sect; <HI>LXXIX.</HI> A new treaty between France and Eng|land. &sect; <HI>LXXX.</HI> The emperor makes overtures to the king of England. &sect; <HI>LXXXI.</HI> Henry makes fre&s;h demands upon the emperor. &sect; <HI>LXXXII.</HI> Charles tampers with cardinal Wol&s;ey. &sect; <HI>LXXXIII.</HI> Affairs of Italy.</P>
